		<a name="top" id="top"></a>
		<div id="siteNotice"><script type='text/javascript'>if (wgNotice != '') document.writeln(wgNotice);</script></div>		<h1 id="firstHeading" class="firstHeading">Silk Road</h1>
		<div id="bodyContent">
			<h3 id="siteSub">From Wikipedia, the free encyclopedia</h3>
			<div id="contentSub"></div>
									<div id="jump-to-nav">Jump to: <a href="#column-one">navigation</a>, <a href="#searchInput">search</a></div>			<!-- start content -->
			<div class="dablink">For other uses, see <a href="/wiki/Silk_Road_(disambiguation)" title="Silk Road (disambiguation)">Silk Road (disambiguation)</a>.</div>
<div class="thumb tright">
<div class="thumbinner" style="width:302px;"><a href="/wiki/File:Silk_Route_extant.JPG" class="image" title="The Silk Road extending from Southern Europe through Arabia, Somalia, Egypt, Persia, India and Java until it reaches China."><img alt="" src="http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/b/b9/Silk_Route_extant.JPG/300px-Silk_Route_extant.JPG" width="300" height="195" border="0" class="thumbimage" /></a>
<div class="thumbcaption">
<div class="magnify"><a href="/wiki/File:Silk_Route_extant.JPG" class="internal" title="Enlarge"><img src="/skins-1.5/common/images/magnify-clip.png" width="15" height="11" alt="" /></a></div>
The Silk Road extending from Southern <a href="/wiki/Europe" title="Europe">Europe</a> through <a href="/wiki/Arabia" title="Arabia" class="mw-redirect">Arabia</a>, <a href="/wiki/Somalia" title="Somalia">Somalia</a>, <a href="/wiki/Egypt" title="Egypt">Egypt</a>, <a href="/wiki/Persia" title="Persia" class="mw-redirect">Persia</a>, <a href="/wiki/India" title="India">India</a> and <a href="/wiki/Java" title="Java">Java</a> until it reaches <a href="/wiki/China" title="China">China</a>.</div>
</div>
</div>
<p>The silk road is an extensive interconnected network of <a href="/wiki/Trade_route" title="Trade route">trade routes</a> across the Asian continent connecting East, South, and Western Asia with the Mediterranean world, including North Africa and Europe.</p>
